-- Nissan's U.S. Plants to Resume Normal Operation Today after Parts Shortage
-- Alan Ohnsman
-- 2010-07-19T23:42:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/nissan-s-u-s-plants-to-resume-normal-operation-today-after-parts-shortage.html

          
          
             Nissan Motor Co.’s plants in
Tennessee and Mississippi will resume normal operation today,
Steve Parrett, a spokesman at the company’s North American
manufacturing unit, said by phone today.  
 Plants in Japan resumed production yesterday, he said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Ohnsman in Los Angeles at 
 aohnsman@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        